article.description: — Sam Mennenga scored 23 points as Davidson beat Old Dominion 66-61 on Sunday.
article.headline: Mennenga scores 23, Davidson beats Old Dominion 66-61
article.linkText: Mennenga scores 23, Davidson beats Old Dominion 66-61
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. -- — Sam Mennenga scored 23 points as Davidson beat Old Dominion 66-61 on Sunday. Mennenga added seven rebounds for the Wildcats (5-1). Foster Loyer scored 22 points and added 10 rebounds. David Skogman made all seven of his free throws and scored 13. The Monarchs (3-3) were led in scoring by Ben Stanley, who finished with 20 points and 10 rebounds. Old Dominion also got 11 points and five assists from Chaunce Jenkins. Tyreek Scott-Grayson finished with 10 points and five assists. Loyer put up 10 points in the first half for Davidson, who led 32-23 at intermission. Mennenga’s 16-point second half helped Davidson close out the victory. NEXT UP Davidson next plays Friday against San Francisco at home, and Old Dominion will host East Carolina on Saturday. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
